        "TextSection": {
            "TextSectionType": "Definition",
            "Contents": "A rare neuronal ceroid lipofuscinosis characterized classically by late infantile-onset (5-10 years) with rapid disease progression myoclonus visual loss and progressive intellectual disability (commonly observed within 2-5 years of seizure onset). Spasticity dystonic posturing tremors and other extrapyramidal signs are also reported in these patients. Less frequently the disease can manifest with intractable tonic-clonic or complex partial seizures without myoclonous progressive intellectual disability and variable visual deficit blindness being infrequent. This condition also known as Northern epilepsy is milder and slow progressing compared to the classical form of the disease."
        },
